        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[Personalizing Docusaurus]]></title>
            <link>https://www.laurentlao.com/blog/setup-styling-docusaurus</link>
            <guid>setup-styling-docusaurus</guid>
            <pubDate>Sat, 12 Mar 2022 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[Phew, just finished the first draft of the personalization of my website. I chose the Nord palette since my development environment also uses that colour palette. This means that having my documentation website open right next to my IDE results in a single design language and is very aesthetically pleasing.]]></description>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Phew, just finished the first draft of the personalization of my website. I chose the <a href="https://www.nordtheme.com/docs/colors-and-palettes" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Nord palette</a> since my development environment also uses that colour palette. This means that having my documentation website open right next to my IDE results in a single design language and is very aesthetically pleasing.</p><p>Since I started with the <code>classic</code> template from Docusaurus, a lot of the theming of my website was already done, but it followed Docusaurus's colour palette. After some inspection with the browser and reading this <a href="https://theochu.com/docusaurus/styling/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">blog</a>, I started to understand how the CSS is handled in Docusaurus.</p><p>I also experimented with the <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/typewriter-effect" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">typewriter-effect</a> library and imported it as a React component to act as my main header page (and add a little flair).</p>]]></content:encoded>
            <category>web dev</category>
            <category>docusaurus</category>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[First blog post with Docusaurus!]]></title>
            <link>https://www.laurentlao.com/blog/first-blog-post</link>
            <guid>first-blog-post</guid>
            <pubDate>Fri, 11 Mar 2022 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[After some time familiarizing myself with React, I decided to ditch my old docsify-based website and transitioned over to Docusaurus.]]></description>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>After some time familiarizing myself with React, I decided to ditch my <a href="https://github.com/laurent-lao/guides" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">old docsify-based</a> website and transitioned over to Docusaurus.</p><p>With this new change to Docusaurus, I can add custom React elements and custom pages, while keeping the ability to write and publish with Markdown. This makes it very useful for a personal website like mine.</p><p>There are many <a href="https://docusaurus.io/showcase" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">other websites</a> built with Docusaurus (like <a href="https://jestjs.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Jest</a> and <a href="https://reactnative.dev/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">React Native</a>) since working with Markdown files when documenting or taking notes is far less verbose than with HTML.</p><p>Below you will find detailed instructions as to how to create a website such as mine very quickly.</p><h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_mojV" id="create-a-docusaurus-website">Create a Docusaurus website<a class="hash-link" href="#create-a-docusaurus-website" title="Direct link to heading">​</a></h2><p>If you wish for your Docusaurus website to point at <code>https://username.github.io/</code> like mine, you must create a Github repository named <code>username.github.io</code>. Otherwise, it will create it at <code>https://username.github.io/reponame/</code></p><ul><li><p>Create an empty Github Repository (e.g. <code>laurent-lao.github.io</code>)</p></li><li><p>Create the Docusaurus application in your local machine using this command </p><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-text codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#F8F8F2;background-color:#282A36"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">npx create-docusaurus@latest laurent-lao.github.io classic</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div></li><li><p>Navigate to the new application (<code>cd laurent-lao.github.io</code>)</p></li><li><p>Init it as a Git directory </p><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-text codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#F8F8F2;background-color:#282A36"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">git init</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div></li><li><p>Edit the <code>docusaurus.config.js</code> with the proper information</p><ul><li>Add a <code>deploymentBranch: 'gh-pages'</code> property to the file</li><li>Add a <code>trailingSlash: false</code> property to the file</li></ul><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-jsx theme-code-block"><div style="color:#F8F8F2;background-color:#282A36" class="codeBlockTitle_BvAR">/docusaurus.config.js</div><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx jsx"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-jsx codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#F8F8F2;background-color:#282A36"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token keyword" style="color:rgb(189, 147, 249);font-style:italic">const</span><span class="token plain"> config </span><span class="token operator">=</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:rgb(248, 248, 242)">{</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">  </span><span class="token literal-property property">title</span><span class="token operator">:</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token string" style="color:rgb(255, 121, 198)">'Laurent Lao'</span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:rgb(248, 248, 242)">,</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">  </span><span class="token literal-property property">tagline</span><span class="token operator">:</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token string" style="color:rgb(255, 121, 198)">'Personal Website'</span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:rgb(248, 248, 242)">,</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">  </span><span class="token literal-property property">url</span><span class="token operator">:</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token string" style="color:rgb(255, 121, 198)">'https://laurent-lao.github.io'</span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:rgb(248, 248, 242)">,</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">  </span><span class="token literal-property property">baseUrl</span><span class="token operator">:</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token string" style="color:rgb(255, 121, 198)">'/'</span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:rgb(248, 248, 242)">,</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">  </span><span class="token literal-property property">onBrokenLinks</span><span class="token operator">:</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token string" style="color:rgb(255, 121, 198)">'throw'</span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:rgb(248, 248, 242)">,</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">  </span><span class="token literal-property property">onBrokenMarkdownLinks</span><span class="token operator">:</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token string" style="color:rgb(255, 121, 198)">'warn'</span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:rgb(248, 248, 242)">,</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line docusaurus-highlight-code-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">  </span><span class="token literal-property property">trailingSlash</span><span class="token operator">:</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token boolean">false</span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:rgb(248, 248, 242)">,</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">  </span><span class="token literal-property property">favicon</span><span class="token operator">:</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token string" style="color:rgb(255, 121, 198)">'img/favicon.ico'</span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:rgb(248, 248, 242)">,</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">  </span><span class="token literal-property property">organizationName</span><span class="token operator">:</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token string" style="color:rgb(255, 121, 198)">'laurent-lao'</span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:rgb(248, 248, 242)">,</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token comment" style="color:rgb(98, 114, 164)">// Usually your GitHub org/user name.</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">  </span><span class="token literal-property property">projectName</span><span class="token operator">:</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token string" style="color:rgb(255, 121, 198)">'laurent-lao.github.io'</span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:rgb(248, 248, 242)">,</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token comment" style="color:rgb(98, 114, 164)">// Usually your repo name.</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line docusaurus-highlight-code-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">  </span><span class="token literal-property property">deploymentBranch</span><span class="token operator">:</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token string" style="color:rgb(255, 121, 198)">'gh-pages'</span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:rgb(248, 248, 242)">,</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div></li><li><p>Execute <code>git commit -am "npx create-docusarus@lastest"</code> to stage and commit the newly created files</p></li><li><p>Link the local repo with the remote and push it</p><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#F8F8F2;background-color:#282A36"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token comment" style="color:rgb(98, 114, 164)"># Execute this</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain"></span><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(80, 250, 123)">git</span><span class="token plain"> remote </span><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(80, 250, 123)">add</span><span class="token plain"> origin git@github.com:laurent-lao/laurent-lao.github.io.git</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain"></span><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(80, 250, 123)">git</span><span class="token plain"> branch -M main</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain"></span><span class="token function" style="color:rgb(80, 250, 123)">git</span><span class="token plain"> push -u origin main</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div></li><li><p>Modify the website to your liking</p></li><li><p>Finally, deploy it with <code>npm run deploy</code></p></li><li><p>You might have to configure the deployment through Github by going to <code>Settings -&gt; Pages</code> and change the branch to "gh-pages"</p></li></ul><h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_mojV" id="custom-domain">Custom Domain<a class="hash-link" href="#custom-domain" title="Direct link to heading">​</a></h2><p>After the initial setup is complete and some content is added, it might be time to use a custom domain for you Docusaurus website. Nothing wrong with a .github.io suffix, but it is nice to have a custom domain.</p><p>There is instructions <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/pages/configuring-a-custom-domain-for-your-github-pages-site/about-custom-domains-and-github-pages" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">here</a> from the GitHub Docs. I personally use Hover for my domains and <a href="https://nickymarino.com/2018/07/29/hover-github-pages/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">this guide</a> helped me get set up.</p>]]></content:encoded>
